533,http://www.armslist.com/posts/541533,For Sale:  5.45X39 RUSSIAN AK-74 + 700 RDS AMMO.,"NW OKC, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma",$ 850,"Listed On: Saturday, September 1, 2012",Rifles,Saiga                                                                                ,5.45x39mm                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"Semi auto civilian version of Russian military AK-74.  Made by Izhmash (Saiga), in the same factory, by the same workers, who make the AK for the Russian military.

The Russians invented the famous AK-47 (7.62X39 caliber) and accepted it into service as their primary weapon in 1947.  It worked well for them as it was very simple and ultra reliable in the worst possible conditions. Although only considered a 300 meter caliber, it was a great improvement over their obsolete rifles in firepower and handling.

But... there were some shortcomings with the 7.62X39 round.  Russian military leaders wanted greater range (500 meters +), more accuracy, lighter weight, less recoil, and MORE terminal effectiveness.  They got ALL of these improvements with the 5.45X39 cartridge.  (Google it.)

The 5.45X39 cartridge proved to be so successful that the Russians adopted it in 1974 (nearly FOURTY years ago), and never looked back.  That is why they gave their old 7.62X39 AK-47s to dictators and revolutionaries all over the world.

The 1st major combat the AK-74 saw was the Russian invasion of Afghanistan in the 1970s.  Locals, facing the 5.45X39 cartridge were amazed by its awesome power.  They called it the ""POISON BULLET"", because of the incredible effectiveness of this round.

5.45X39 is the cheapest center fire ammo on the planet.  With Tula, Wolf, Baurnal, Brownbear, Slilverbear, Hornady (and others?), availability is excellent. All of the above are NON-CORROSIVE ammo.  Military surplus (corrosive primer) ammo can be found in sealed cans of 1080 rds for $120.  That's less than half the cost of 7.62X39, and about a third as much as quality 5.56.
Rifle comes with chrome lined chamber/barrel, factory equiped (built on) scope/red dot mount, 30 rd magazine, and 700 rounds of premium Silverbear (non-corrosive) ammo.
Very low round count... around 120 rds through it. Kicks less that an AR!
Perfect for fun plinking, plenty accurate for the range, and very reassuring as the ultimate family defense.
Face to face only."
